dataset.comment: Spinup: restart files from end of experiment 20C3M (corresponding realisation). Anthropogenic (GHGs, sulfate aerosol direct and first indirect effects) and natural forcing (solar irradiance and volcanic activity implemented through varying solar constant) are used for the 20C3M simulations.

dataset.attr: MIUB model output prepared for IPCC Fourth Assessment 550 ppm stabilization experiment (SRES B1)
ECHO-G(1999): atmosphere: ECHAM4 (T30L19) with partial sea ice with flux aggregation and continental ice sheet discharge incl. latent heat; ocean: HOPE-G (T42+equator refinement/L20); sea ice: HOPE-G

ECHAM4: E. Roeckner et al., 1996, The atmospheric general circulation model ECHAM4, MPI Report No. 218; HOPE-G: Legutke and Maier-Reimer, 1999, Climatology of the HOPE-G Global Ocean General Circulation Model, DKRZ Techn. Report 21; ECHO-G: Min et al., 2004: Climatology and internal variability in a 1000-year control simulation with the coupled climate model ECHO-G, Tellus A, in print.
